00:48:20.735 --> 00:48:22.360
HADLEY FREEMAN: It's
all I think about.

00:48:22.360 --> 00:48:23.230
It's really tragic.

00:48:23.230 --> 00:48:26.630
So I have two-year-old twins.

00:48:26.630 --> 00:48:29.120
So they don't really have
attention span for anything

00:48:29.120 --> 00:48:31.790
beyond a two minute "Peppa
Pig" video at the moment.

00:48:31.790 --> 00:48:34.142
So they're twin boys as
well, which is obviously

00:48:34.142 --> 00:48:36.350
slightly different for me,
although I very much think

00:48:36.350 --> 00:48:37.650
that boys and girls should
just watch the same movies.

00:48:37.650 --> 00:48:38.690
There shouldn't be
these kinds of limits.

00:48:38.690 --> 00:48:40.310
But I do get that
certain things grab

00:48:40.310 --> 00:48:43.160
boys' attention quicker than
maybe grab girls' attention.

00:48:43.160 --> 00:48:46.010
So for example, my first movie
from that era that I saw was,

00:48:46.010 --> 00:48:48.290
I believe, "Ferris
Bueller's Day Off."

00:48:48.290 --> 00:48:50.653
Whereas I already know,
from my boyfriend's stuff,

00:48:50.653 --> 00:48:52.486
the first '80s movie
they'll probably go see

00:48:52.486 --> 00:48:55.340
is going to be "Back to the
Future' or "Indiana Jones."

00:48:55.340 --> 00:48:57.537
Those kind of more
actiony things.

00:48:57.537 --> 00:48:59.870
Whereas I got to those a
little bit later, and obviously

00:48:59.870 --> 00:49:00.260
I loved them.

00:49:00.260 --> 00:49:00.900
There was no difference.

00:49:00.900 --> 00:49:01.940
There shouldn't be a
difference between what

00:49:01.940 --> 00:49:02.820
boys and girls watch.

00:49:02.820 --> 00:49:03.820
Let me just stress that.

00:49:03.820 --> 00:49:06.954
But I do think they'll probably
enjoy "Back to the Future"

00:49:06.954 --> 00:49:08.870
earlier than they might
enjoy "Ferris Bueller"

00:49:08.870 --> 00:49:09.860
and "The Breakfast Club."

00:49:09.860 --> 00:49:12.360
JON SKEET: It's an important
question about introducing kids

00:49:12.360 --> 00:49:13.940
to films, "Star Wars."

00:49:13.940 --> 00:49:16.980
Do you start with Episode 4 or
do you start with Episode 1?

00:49:16.980 --> 00:49:19.063
HADLEY FREEMAN: I get so
confused with the episode

00:49:19.063 --> 00:49:20.490
numbers at this point.

00:49:20.490 --> 00:49:22.370
You've got to start
with Episode 4, right?

00:49:22.370 --> 00:49:22.505
JON SKEET: Thank you.

00:49:22.505 --> 00:49:22.550
You can stay.

00:49:22.550 --> 00:49:23.930
HADLEY FREEMAN: I mean,
actually my first Star Wars

00:49:23.930 --> 00:49:24.971
was "Return of the Jedi."

00:49:24.971 --> 00:49:27.614
I think that might have been the
first movie I saw in a cinema.

00:49:27.614 --> 00:49:28.780
It was "Return of the Jedi."

00:49:28.780 --> 00:49:29.485
JON SKEET: Jinx.

00:49:29.485 --> 00:49:30.610
HADLEY FREEMAN: Oh, really?

00:49:30.610 --> 00:49:31.370
JON SKEET: Yeah, absolutely.

00:49:31.370 --> 00:49:31.482
HADLEY FREEMAN: Funny.

00:49:31.482 --> 00:49:33.662
And I loved it, because I
love the ewoks, obviously.

